# {{project_name}}

Email + password + machine-bound token login server. Same shape as DataBrick's.

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Body |
|---|---|---|
| POST | /signup  | `{ email, password }` |
| POST | /login   | `{ email, password, machine_id }` |
| POST | /verify  | `{ token, machine_id }` |
| POST | /refresh | `{ token }` |
| POST | /logout  | `{ token }` |
| GET  | /health  | |

`machine_id` is anything your client generates and stores (e.g. `crypto.randomUUID()` on first launch). Tokens are bound to it — copying a token to a different machine fails verify.

